{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 180°C and line 2 baking trays with baking paper.","Place chocolate and butter in mixing bowl then heat <b>3 min\/50°C\/speed <b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and heat again <b>2 min\/50°C\/speed <b>. Transfer warm chocolate butter to a bowl and set aside.","Insert butterfly whisk. Place eggs, sugar and vanilla then whisk <b>3 min\/speed 4<b> until light and fluffy.","Mix <b>1 min 30 sec\/speed 2<b> while very slowly pouring the melted chocolate butter through the hole in the TM lid onto the egg mixture.","Add flour and baking powder then mix <b>10 sec\/speed 2<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and mix again <b>10 sec\/speed 2<b>. Remove butterfly whisk.","Spoon 12 portions out onto prepared baking trays, leaving plenty of space between each scoop. The mixture will be quite loose at this stage. Sprinkle with a few sea salt flakes if desired. Bake 10-12 minutes (180°C) then allow to cool completely on the tray before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["220 g dark chocolate, small pieces or callets","30 g salted butter","2 large eggs","130 g granulated sugar","½ tsp real vanilla extract","35 g plain flour","¼ tsp baking powder","sea salt flakes, for sprinkling (optional)"]}],"id":"r80566","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-OvxOPQSnw8s\/XZanv9F2UtI\/AAAAAAAAhDk\/X2xyCB1dZ3s5HedHjc4GBuUbVVHVjPnHgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_TnPvHUttnob6R-Rt.png","title":"Ben's Chocolate Cookies","publishedAt":"2015-05-13T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"2.4 g","fat":"8.3 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"24.8 g","calories":"766 kJ \/ 183 kcal"},"usefulItems":"2 baking trays and baking paper, 2 baking trays, baking paper, oven","hintsAndTricks":["This recipe is from Benjamin Chocolatier (Ben Axford), who has used Thermomix for many years both as a chef and as a chocolatier.","After mixing in the flour and baking powder in Step 4, <strong>remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>, add dried cherries, pecans, chocolate chips or a mixture (75 g total weight), then stir <strong>4 sec\/\/speed 2<\/strong> to mix them in before shaping and baking."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","40m","12 portions"]}